          <p>Cryptography means the study of encryption algorithms. These encryption alogrithms can be classified into several categories. On the above picture, these classifications are shown in a simplified form.<br><br>
          <h5>1. By Encryption process:</h5> Either the algoritms can be substitutional or transposition. Substituional techniques replace one character with another according to the process where as transposition techniques change the position of the characters.<br><br>
          <h5>2. By number of keys:</h5>Either the algortihm can be single key or double key algortihm. The ciphers such as ceaser cipher, monoalphabetic ciphers, polyalphabetic ciphers, hill cipher these are single key or symmetric key algorithms where as a famous double key or asymmetric algorithm is RSA Algorithm.<br><br>
